  "prompt": "What is the process to get a job at Wipro?",
  "response": "Getting a job at Wipro typically involves several steps:\n\n1. **Research and Preparation:**\n   - Understand the company's culture, values, and business areas.\n   - Prepare your resume, highlighting relevant skills and experiences.\n\n2. **Application:**\n   - Visit the Wipro careers website or job portals where Wipro posts openings.\n   - Submit your application online, including your resume and cover letter.\n\n3. **Assessment Tests:**\n   - If your application is shortlisted, you may be required to take aptitude tests, which can include logical reasoning, quantitative ability, and verbal ability.\n   - Some roles might require technical tests relevant to the job.\n\n4. **Technical Interview:**\n   - If you pass the assessment tests, you will be invited for a technical interview where you will be assessed on your technical knowledge and problem-solving skills.\n   - Be prepared for questions related to your field of expertise, past projects, and practical scenarios.\n\n5. **HR Interview:**\n   - If you clear the technical interview, the next step is usually an HR interview.\n   - This interview focuses on your personality, cultural fit, career aspirations, and ability to work in a team.\n\n6. **Offer and Onboarding:**\n   - If you successfully pass all interview rounds, you will receive an offer letter.\n   - Review the offer, negotiate if necessary, and accept the offer.\n   - Once you accept, Wipro will guide you through the onboarding process, which includes documentation and orientation.\n\nThroughout the process, it's essential to stay professional, be prepared to discuss your experiences and skills, and show enthusiasm for the role and the company.",
